{
  "stem": "1858.4",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 322.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "I hope she was.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Anyway, we worked in the factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "There were POWs working, British, as well as Russian.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "They lived in different camps, not under the conditions that we did.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But, nevertheless, they were prisoners.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "There was one British-- or rather South African prisoner that-- I will never forget his name-- he worked across from me in a building that his window was facing mine.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And somehow, he tried to signal to me through the window that he-- I am trying to send you something to eat.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And through a French prisoner of war, or there were French men working in the factory too, and they brought the supplies to my machines.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And through that man, he sent me a tiny little, tiny square, of chocolate, which I haven't had chocolate for so many years, and also a picture of his little sister, which I have until today, in a scout uniform.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he wrote that I remind him so much of his little sister.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "I remember his name until today.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "After the war, I tried to contact him.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I don't know if he survived because the winters were brutal for the soldiers from Africa.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "His name was George C.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Hays.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And his address was P-O-U-G-I-E, South Africa.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "I can never forget his name for that tiny bit of chocolate that probably didn't mean so much to anyone.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But to know that the man thought of me and wanted to send it to me, I could never forget someone who opened his heart, who thought that there was a little girl and I am going to give her something that she never had for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "So it was acts like this that you never forget.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
